name: Steamer leather travel bag
description: A lovely Louis Vuitton steamer 35 travel bag in monogram canvas and natural tan leather, made in France in the early quarter of the 20th century. Steamer bags have been produced by Louis Vuitton for over 120 years. In 1901, the company introduced the simple canvas and leather steamer bag, whose squat, squarish proportions were based on the mailbags used in the Americas. Here was a bag that could be hung on the back of a cabin door, carried around on deck or stored away in the hold inside one of Louis Vuitton’s famous packing cases. The design has remained basically unchanged since then, as popular now as they were then. A nice piece for the seasoned collector. Sale number 891985. One side strap is missing. Heave leather wear throughout.
